Document: OpenXRFrameSynthesisExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrframesynthesisextension.rst
Summary: Available methods for the OpenXRFrameSynthesisExtension class and their parameters.

- Method: is_available() → bool (const)
- Method: skip_next_frame() → void

Note: The is_available method is marked as const, indicating it does not modify the object's state. The skip_next_frame method has no return value and is used to control frame synthesis behavior.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRFrameSynthesisExtension  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrframesynthesisextension.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring frame synthesis behavior in OpenXR extensions.  

enabled (bool): Enable frame synthesis. When true motion vector and depth data is provided to the XR runtime. Set via set_enabled(value: bool), get via is_enabled(). Default: false.  

relax_frame_interval (bool): If true informs the XR runtime we will be providing frames at a greatly reduced rate. Enable this when your application runs at low framerates and wishes to inject multiple reprojected frames. Set via set_relax_frame_interval(value: bool), get via get_relax_frame_interval(). Default: false.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRFrameSynthesisExtension  
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrframesynthesisextension.rst  
Summary: Two methods for checking frame synthesis availability and controlling frame skipping in XR rendering.  

Method: is_available() → bool  
Returns true if frame synthesis is enabled in project settings and the current XR runtime supports frame synthesis. The value will only be valid after OpenXR has been initialized. Note: This method's result is only reliable once OpenXR is fully initialized.  

Method: skip_next_frame() → void  
Queues the next frame to be skipped when supplying motion vector and depth data. Call this after teleporting the player or similar actions that move the player to prevent incorrect reprojection results caused by sudden positional changes.